The '''High Judicial and Prosecutorial Council''' of [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]] is a national institution responsible for many aspects of the [[judicial system]] Bosnia and Herzegovina.  It appoints, trains, and disciplines [[judge]]s, prosecutors in [[The Prosecutor Office of Bosnia and Herzegovina]] in and is responsible for advising other levels of government about judicial budgets and administration.

